UML:TaggedValue.value: The Mission Analysis package provides a general construct for describing the system from the perspective of the general mission. The Mission Block Model provides one of the earliest forms of context in the development process. The context block diagram is a very useful too in describing the necessary components of the system. The Mission Block Model is a starting point for defining the structural relationships between the high level blocks within the feature, system, sub-system, component, or external system.
